text: Seletar is located in the North-Eastern region of Singapore. Seletar derives its name from Orang Seletar, a Malay subgroup who were indigenous to the area. This area generally refers to a region by the Ponggol River to the east, the Seletar River to the west, Ang Mo Kio to the south, and the Straits of Johore to the north. == References == Category:Places in Singapore
title: Seletar
